,\"deleted_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:23:00.287387199-08:00\",\"deleted_by\":\"batch delete\",\"delete_reason\":\"batch delete\",\"original_type\":\"task\"}\n    30→{\"id\":\"cloche-52f\",\"title\":\"Run and Capture domain types\",\"description\":\"Run, StepExecution, RunState types with lifecycle methods. See implementation plan Task 3.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.349277238-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T12:05:00.4109792-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-20T12:05:00.4109792-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Run, StepExecution types with lifecycle methods\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-52f\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-fv2\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.350429185-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n    31→{\"id\":\"cloche-59l\",\"title\":\"Daemon capture storage\",\"description\":\"Update trackRun() to extract and store new fields from status messages. Set ProjectDir on run record. See Task 7 in docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"estimated_minutes\":15,\"created_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:07:35.32137865-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:41:50.493099344-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:41:50.493099344-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"labels\":[\"evolution\"],\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-59l\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-d3p\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:09:29.744330962-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"},{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-59l\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-myv\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:09:29.78002563-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n    32→{\"id\":\"cloche-5bj\",\"title\":\"Update example workflows\",\"description\":\"Rename pass to success in all example workflows. Update fix step results. Update wiring accordingly. Implementation plan Task 11.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:25:12.45023414-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:54:37.915671326-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:54:37.915674693-08:00\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-5bj\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-2nb\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:25:12.452228195-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"},{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-5bj\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-88j\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:25:12.45529421-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n    33→{\"id\":\"cloche-5dd\",\"title\":\"Unify workflow engine between cloched and cloche-agent\",\"description\":\"cloched and cloche-agent both parse and execute workflows but use completely different code paths. The host runner in the orchestrator is a bespoke reimplementation of what cloche-agent already does. Refactor so both share the same workflow parser, graph walker, and step runner — the only difference should be the environment (host vs container). This eliminates the duplicated logic that keeps breaking.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-09T10:10:31.885481297-07:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-09T12:40:35.55677421-07:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-09T12:40:35.55677421-07:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-5dd\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-r96\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-09T10:11:19.589368657-07:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n    34→{\"id\":\"cloche-5jq\",\"title\":\"Update Run model for concurrent steps\",\"description\":\"Replace CurrentStep with ActiveSteps []string in domain.Run. Update RecordStepStart/RecordStepComplete. Fix all callers. Implementation plan Task 9.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:25:12.369774283-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:54:37.880612017-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:54:37.880615303-08:00\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-5jq\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-1r0\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:25:12.370864647-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n    35→{\"id\":\"cloche-5yt\",\"title\":\"Update runner and status reporting\",\"description\":\"- type: task\",\"status\":\"tombstone\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:21:14.718466959-08:00\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:23:00.287387199-08:00\",\"deleted_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:23:00.287387199-08:00\",\"deleted_by\":\"batch delete\",\"delete_reason\":\"batch delete\",\"original_type\":\"task\"}\n    36→{\"id\":\"cloche-6e9\",\"title\":\"Add cloche delete command for container removal\",\"description\":\"Add 'cloche delete \\u003ccontainer-or-run-id\\u003e' CLI command. Accepts Docker container name/ID or run ID. Calls daemon via new DeleteContainer gRPC RPC. Daemon calls docker rm and updates SQLite. Single container at a time. See docs/plans/2026-03-03-next-features-design.md §5.\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"cloche delete accepts container ID or run ID. Container is removed. SQLite record updated.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T10:41:59.761005025-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-03T12:52:21.676887164-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-03T12:52:21.676887164-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-6e9\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-toz\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T10:45:38.582029929-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n    37→{\"id\":\"cloche-6lt\",\"title\":\"Implement merge agent (LLM-driven merge in git worktree)\",\"description\":\"Merge agent runs on the host in a git worktree. Given a branch name, it: creates a worktree, pulls latest main, merges the feature branch, resolves conflicts via LLM, runs validation if configured, merges to main on success. On success: cleans up worktree and deletes the branch. On failure: marks merge as failed, preserves branch, notifies via dashboard/indicator lights. See docs/plans/2026-03-03-next-features-design.md §1 Merge Queue.\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"Merge agent creates worktree, merges branch, resolves conflicts. Success: branch deleted, worktree cleaned. Failure: branch preserved, merge marked failed.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T11:00:40.12111266-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-03T17:08:13.380584248-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-03T17:08:13.380584248-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-6lt\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-req\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T11:01:15.431388653-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n    38→{\"id\":\"cloche-6vs\",\"title\":\"Add container status to dashboard run detail page\",\"description\":\"Run detail page shows whether the container is still available. If so, shows a 'Delete container' button. Project overview shows count of retained containers. See docs/plans/2026-03-03-next-features-design.md §5.\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"Run detail shows container availability. Delete button works. Project cards show retained container count.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T10:42:30.941042115-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-03T12:52:21.748717246-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-03T12:52:21.748717246-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-6vs\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-toz\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T10:45:38.540717126-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n    39→{\"id\":\"cloche-76q\",\"title\":\"Full integration test pass\",\"description\":\"Run go test and go vet to verify everything works end to end. Fix any remaining issues. Implementation plan Task 12.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:25:12.493851051-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T21:02:28.815866163-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-20T21:02:28.815868458-08:00\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-76q\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-h9t\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:25:12.495079326-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"},{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-76q\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-5bj\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:25:12.496694304-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n    40→{\"id\":\"cloche-78b\",\"title\":\"Bug: Orchestrator ignores beads dependency graph — dispatches blocked tasks\",\"description\":\"The orchestrator's ListReady call returned tasks that have unsatisfied blocking dependencies. Tasks like cloche-07g (blocked by cloche-2cc, cloche-9ea, cloche-dzz) and cloche-208 (blocked by cloche-07g) were dispatched even though their blockers were still open.\\n\\nEither the beads tracker's ListReady implementation doesn't check the dependency graph, or the orchestrator is calling the wrong method. This caused tasks to run before their prerequisites were complete, leading to incorrect implementations and merge conflicts.\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"- ListReady only returns tasks whose blocking dependencies are all closed/completed\\n- Tasks with open blockers are never dispatched by the orchestrator\\n- Verify with a test: create task A blocking task B, confirm B is not returned by ListReady\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":0,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T13:15:00.028458264-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-06T14:49:12.854707838-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-06T14:49:12.854707838-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\"}\n    41→{\"id\":\"cloche-7qu\",\"title\":\"Add OutputMapping and OutputPath types to domain\",\"description\":\"Add OutputMapping (EnvVar + OutputPath) and OutputPath (list of PathSegments) types to internal/domain/workflow.go. Add OutputMap field to Wire struct. Implement Evaluate([]byte) method on OutputPath that navigates JSON using field access and array indexing. Unit test path evaluation.\",\"design\":\"docs/plans/2026-03-09-wire-output-mapping-design.md\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-09T15:14:57.207446372-07:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-09T15:42:37.814276279-07:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-09T15:42:37.814276279-07:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"labels\":[\"domain\",\"dsl\"],\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-7qu\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-r3e\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-09T15:15:10.73732184-07:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n    42→{\"id\":\"cloche-88j\",\"title\":\"Update prompt adapter to use result extraction\",\"description\":\"Inject result selection instructions into assembled prompt and use protocol.ExtractResult to parse LLM output. Remove resultOrDefault. Update tests. Implementation plan Task 5.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:24:52.067985163-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:39:43.966435416-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:39:43.966438292-08:00\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-88j\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-8ze\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:24:52.069151601-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n    43→{\"id\":\"cloche-8bi\",\"title\":\"DSL lexer\",\"description\":\"Tokenizer for the Cloche workflow DSL. Token types, Lexer with NextToken(). See implementation plan Task 4.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.389025368-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T12:05:00.44646389-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-20T12:05:00.44646389-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Lexer with all token types, comments, arrows\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-8bi\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-fv2\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.390262837-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n    44→{\"id\":\"cloche-8td\",\"title\":\"Add domain types for Collect\",\"description\":\"- type: task\",\"status\":\"tombstone\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:21:14.711618079-08:00\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:23:00.287387199-08:00\",\"deleted_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:23:00.287387199-08:00\",\"deleted_by\":\"batch delete\",\"delete_reason\":\"batch delete\",\"original_type\":\"task\"}\n    45→{\"id\":\"cloche-8ze\",\"title\":\"Add result extraction protocol\",\"description\":\"Create internal/protocol/result.go with ExtractResult function that scans output for CLOCHE_RESULT marker. Last marker wins. Returns clean output with markers stripped. Implementation plan Task 3.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:24:24.152958495-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:31:16.342627663-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:31:16.342630989-08:00\"}\n    46→{\"id\":\"cloche-8zs\",\"title\":\"Chore: initialize .cloche/version in cloche project\",\"description\":\"After cloche-9ea merges, create .cloche/version with content '1' in the cloche project repo. Commit and push so the file is tracked. The daemon will then start incrementing it on future evolution cycles.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T11:42:26.76039592-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-06T14:24:45.390243196-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-06T14:24:45.390243196-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-8zs\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-9ea\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T11:42:48.08690651-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n    47→{\"id\":\"cloche-95g\",\"title\":\"gRPC server (daemon side)\",\"description\":\"ClocheServer implementing the gRPC service with RunStore backend. See implementation plan Task 13.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.77088948-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T13:05:56.205201841-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-20T13:05:56.205201841-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-95g\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-49c\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.772095809-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"},{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-95g\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-nq9\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.77372075-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n    48→{\"id\":\"cloche-9ea\",\"title\":\"Project versioning: increment .cloche/version on evolution changes\",\"description\":\"After the evolution pipeline makes any change to workflow or prompt files, increment the integer in .cloche/version. File starts at 1 (created by cloche init). See docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-versioning-design.md.\",\"design\":\"docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-versioning-design.md\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"- .cloche/version is created with content '1' by cloche init\\n- config.LoadVersion(projectDir) reads and returns the version\\n- evolution/orchestrator.go increments the version when len(result.Changes) \\u003e 0\\n- Version is exposed in /api/projects/{name}/info response\\n- .cloche/version is not gitignored\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T11:25:03.406211132-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-07T18:50:08.138606886-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-07T18:50:08.138606886-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\"}\n    49→{\"id\":\"cloche-9lt\",\"title\":\"Move project runs URL to projects/\\u003cproject\\u003e/runs\",\"description\":\"Viewing runs for a project is currently at runs?project=... but should be at projects/\\u003cproject\\u003e/runs for cleaner URL structure.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-07T19:16:54.288923031-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-09T13:27:40.485633014-07:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-09T13:27:40.485633014-07:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\"}\n    50→{\"id\":\"cloche-9ud\",\"title\":\"Evolution Collector stage\",\"description\":\"Gather runs since last evolution, knowledge base, current prompts, current workflow. See Task 9 in docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"estimated_minutes\":20,\"created_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:07:52.658144322-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:34:26.658653494-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:34:26.658653494-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"labels\":[\"evolution\"],\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-9ud\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-sdc\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:09:29.815486827-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83efa890-2574-44c5-a1f7-226ad3f671c0","uuid":"6ca1f847-5e38-4e9c-be18-950999a9d234","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/.beads/issues.jsonl","content":"{\"id\":\"cloche-028\",\"title\":\"Add cloche-base Docker image and simplify default Dockerfile\",\"description\":\"Create docker/cloche-base/Dockerfile: debian:12-slim + git + cloche-agent. Add docker-base Makefile target (tags cloche-base:latest and cloche-base:\\u003cversion\\u003e). Make docker-build depend on docker-base. Simplify the cloche project's .cloche/Dockerfile and the init template to use cloche-base:latest. See docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-base-docker-design.md.\",\"design\":\"docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-base-docker-design.md\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"- docker/cloche-base/Dockerfile exists (debian:12-slim, git, cloche-agent; no node/claude-code)\\n- make docker-base builds cloche-base:latest and cloche-base:\\u003cversion\\u003e\\n- make docker-build depends on docker-base\\n- make install builds and starts correctly\\n- .cloche/Dockerfile simplified to FROM cloche-base:latest + add claude-code\\n- cloche init generates Dockerfile using cloche-base:latest; --image flag renamed to --base-image\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T11:26:28.701191268-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-06T14:24:40.971081943-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-06T14:24:40.971081943-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\"}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-07g\",\"title\":\"Update cloche init with new project scaffolding\",\"description\":\"Update cloche init to create all current project files: config.toml, version, host.cloche, scripts/prepare-prompt.sh. Replace the old gitignore strategy (ignore .cloche/*/ then negate) with the inverse: track everything, explicitly ignore runtime artifacts (.cloche/*-*-*/, .cloche/run-*/, .cloche/attempt_count/). See docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T11:26:28.640735412-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-06T14:24:45.477722406-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-06T14:24:45.477722406-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-07g\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-2cc\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T11:26:28.642105034-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"},{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-07g\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-dzz\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T11:26:28.658281745-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"},{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-07g\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-9ea\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T11:26:28.660178435-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"},{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-07g\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-mk9\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T11:42:47.941084805-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"},{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-07g\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-jj7\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T11:42:48.216963812-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-0aa\",\"title\":\"Evolution Classifier stage\",\"description\":\"LLM-based classification of run prompts into bug/feedback/feature/enhancement/chore. See Task 10 in docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"estimated_minutes\":15,\"created_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:07:52.699618555-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:34:26.694741926-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:34:26.694741926-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"labels\":[\"evolution\"],\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-0aa\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-9ud\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:09:29.850421963-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-0yn\",\"title\":\"TOML config system\",\"description\":\"Add config package with Load() for .cloche/config. Support [evolution] section with enabled, debounce_seconds, min_confidence, max_prompt_bullets. See Task 8 in docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"estimated_minutes\":15,\"created_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:07:35.362293737-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:23:16.797914218-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:23:16.797914218-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"labels\":[\"evolution\"]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-0z1\",\"title\":\"Wire cloche CLI binary\",\"description\":\"CLI client with run/status/list/stop subcommands over gRPC. See implementation plan Task 16.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":0,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.89421394-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T13:22:06.329718638-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-20T13:22:06.329718638-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-0z1\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-nq9\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.895418456-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-0zu\",\"title\":\"Update generic adapter to use result extraction\",\"description\":\"- type: task\",\"status\":\"tombstone\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:21:14.714017336-08:00\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:23:00.287387199-08:00\",\"deleted_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:23:00.287387199-08:00\",\"deleted_by\":\"batch delete\",\"delete_reason\":\"batch delete\",\"original_type\":\"task\"}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-1r0\",\"title\":\"Rewrite engine as DAG walker\",\"description\":\"Replace linear engine loop with concurrent DAG walker. Track active steps, pending collects, and completed results. Goroutines and channels. Validate results against declared list. Fanout and collect support. Implementation plan Task 8.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:25:12.32885009-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:50:29.533256069-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:50:29.533258483-08:00\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-1r0\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-nh0\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:25:12.330042036-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"},{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-1r0\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-cow\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:25:12.33160231-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-1uz\",\"title\":\"Establish host.cloche vs container .cloche convention\",\"description\":\"Formalize the convention: host.cloche contains workflows that run on the host machine (e.g. the main workflow that orchestrates container runs, merges results). All other .cloche files define workflows that run inside containers. Update the DSL docs, workflow loading code, and daemon to enforce this split cleanly.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-09T10:10:40.49233334-07:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-09T10:38:21.033728769-07:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-09T10:38:21.033728769-07:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\"}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-1vi\",\"title\":\"Add project filters to the web dashboard\",\"description\":\"Add project filtering to the web dashboard so runs can be viewed per-project. Display the final directory name from the project path (e.g. 'myproject' from '/home/user/workspace/myproject'). When project names conflict (e.g. foo/bar and baz/bar), show the parent directory to disambiguate (e.g. 'foo/bar' vs 'baz/bar').\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-27T12:35:00.353790595-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-06T08:02:08.60585394-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-06T08:02:08.60585394-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\"}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-208\",\"title\":\"Chore: update .gitignore to new cloche pattern\",\"description\":\"After cloche-07g merges, update .gitignore in the cloche project to use the new pattern: remove old .cloche/*/ negation rules, add .cloche/*-*-*/ and .cloche/run-*/ and .cloche/attempt_count/ as explicit ignores. Commit the change.\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"- .gitignore has .cloche/*-*-*/ (replaces old .cloche/*/)\\n- .gitignore has .cloche/run-*/\\n- .gitignore has .cloche/attempt_count/\\n- Old negation rules (!.cloche/prompts/ etc.) are removed\\n- git status shows no unintended tracked/untracked changes in .cloche/\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T11:42:26.844683774-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-06T14:24:45.521089356-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-06T14:24:45.521089356-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-208\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-07g\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T11:42:48.258587099-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-28m\",\"title\":\"Parse raw JSON log stream into human-readable run history\",\"description\":\"Currently the run logs display raw JSON data from Claude Code's output stream. This makes run history hard to read. Instead, parse the JSON log entries and extract only the meaningful content (assistant text messages, tool call summaries, tool results, errors) to display a clean, human-readable run history.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-08T18:16:25.049718638-07:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-09T13:19:44.354528785-07:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-09T13:19:44.354528785-07:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\"}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-2cc\",\"title\":\"Rename .cloche/config to .cloche/config.toml\",\"description\":\"Rename the per-project settings file from .cloche/config to .cloche/config.toml. No backwards compatibility needed. cloche init creates a default config.toml with all settings documented. See docs/plans/2026-03-06-config-toml-design.md.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T11:25:19.846711541-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-06T14:24:41.043760414-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-06T14:24:41.043760414-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\"}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-2ju\",\"title\":\"Implement orchestration loop in cloched\",\"description\":\"Event-driven orchestration loop inside cloched. Triggers on: daemon startup, run completion, and new cloche orchestrate CLI command. On trigger: for each project with orchestration enabled, query task tracker, check per-project concurrency limits, claim highest-priority task, generate prompt, dispatch run. Per-project config in .cloche/config.toml. See docs/plans/2026-03-03-next-features-design.md §1.\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"Orchestrator triggers on startup, run completion, and manual command. Respects per-project concurrency limits. Dispatches runs for ready tasks.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T10:42:45.361039309-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-03T12:52:21.892779417-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-03T12:52:21.892779417-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-2ju\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-31r\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T10:45:38.705184919-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"},{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-2ju\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-43y\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T10:45:38.745875428-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-2nb\",\"title\":\"Update generic adapter to use result extraction\",\"description\":\"Replace resultOrDefault with protocol.ExtractResult. Marker overrides exit code. Exit 0 = success, non-zero = fail as fallback. Update tests. Implementation plan Task 4.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:24:52.027891556-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:39:43.928824823-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:39:43.928828069-08:00\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-2nb\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-8ze\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:24:52.029049218-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-2sg\",\"title\":\"Add post-run log archival with SQLite indexing\",\"description\":\"On run completion, extract all log files from container to .cloche/\\u003crun-id\\u003e/output/. Write index entries to SQLite (run ID, step name, log file path, size, timestamps). Dashboard and CLI query index and serve file contents on demand. Enhance cloche logs \\u003crun-id\\u003e --step \\u003cname\\u003e filtering. See docs/plans/2026-03-03-next-features-design.md §4.\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"Logs extracted and archived on completion. SQLite index populated. cloche logs --step filtering works.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T10:42:19.148963423-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-03T12:52:21.857300137-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-03T12:52:21.857300137-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-2sg\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-v5x\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T10:45:38.662096666-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-31r\",\"title\":\"Define TaskTracker port and implement Beads adapter\",\"description\":\"Create ports.TaskTracker interface with ListReady, Claim, Complete, Fail methods. Task struct carries ID, title, description, labels, priority. Implement first adapter for Beads. ListReady returns tasks ordered by priority. See docs/plans/2026-03-03-next-features-design.md §1.\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"TaskTracker interface defined. Beads adapter works: lists ready tasks by priority, claims/completes/fails tasks.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T10:42:37.781893815-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-03T11:38:08.233538356-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-03T11:38:08.233538356-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\"}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-38w\",\"title\":\"Bug: Orchestrator does not close beads tasks after successful workflow runs\",\"description\":\"When a workflow run completes successfully, the orchestrator never calls tracker.Complete() to mark the beads task as done. The task stays 'ready' in beads, so subsequent orchestration cycles re-dispatch it indefinitely. This caused duplicate runs and cascading merge conflicts.\\n\\nRoot cause: orchestrator.Run() claims tasks and dispatches runs, but OnRunComplete() only decrements the in-flight counter — it never updates the task's status in the tracker.\\n\\nFix: After a successful workflow run, call pc.Tracker.Complete(ctx, task.ID). After a failed run, call pc.Tracker.Fail(ctx, task.ID). This requires correlating run IDs back to task IDs, which is not currently tracked.\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"- Successful workflow runs mark the associated beads task as completed\\n- Failed workflow runs mark the associated beads task appropriately (fail or reopen)\\n- A task is never dispatched more than once concurrently\\n- Run-to-task mapping is tracked (e.g. in the Run struct or a side map)\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":0,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T13:14:59.985826907-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-06T14:49:12.847791831-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-06T14:49:12.847791831-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\"}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-3hj\",\"title\":\"Audit Logger\",\"description\":\"JSONL append-only log, file snapshots for revert, knowledge base updates. See Task 15 in docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"estimated_minutes\":15,\"created_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:07:52.892498677-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:41:50.566081025-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:41:50.566081025-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"labels\":[\"evolution\"],\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-3hj\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-9ud\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:09:29.989064368-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-3ic\",\"title\":\"Implement per-project health calculator (indicator lights)\",\"description\":\"Domain-level health calculator: given last N runs for a project, return health status (green/yellow/red/grey/blue). Window size configurable per-project, default 5. Green = all passed, Yellow = some failed, Red = all failed, Grey = no runs, Blue = all in-progress. See docs/plans/2026-03-03-next-features-design.md §2.\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"Health function returns correct status for all edge cases. Window size configurable.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T10:42:02.687024565-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-03T11:38:08.131593855-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-03T11:38:08.131593855-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\"}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-3it\",\"title\":\"Wire cloche-agent binary\",\"description\":\"First vertical slice: agent parses workflow file, walks graph, executes steps, streams status. See implementation plan Task 10.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":0,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.640304428-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T12:12:10.062003732-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-20T12:12:10.062003732-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-3it\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-u6c\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.642661493-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"},{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-3it\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-cit\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.645862723-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"},{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-3it\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-ehk\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.648881668-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"},{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-3it\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-hu2\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.65184022-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-3ld\",\"title\":\"Preserve accordion state in web portal log viewer during SSE updates\",\"description\":\"While viewing logs in the web portal, task-specific log output is displayed inside accordion folds. When the run is active, arriving SSE events cause the page to refresh, which resets accordion state and closes any open accordions. Fix this so accordion open/closed state is preserved even as new log data appends via SSE.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-09T14:05:36.298070376-07:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-09T16:49:40.17841768-07:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-09T16:49:40.17841768-07:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"labels\":[\"logs\",\"web-portal\"]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-408\",\"title\":\"Update validation for collects\",\"description\":\"- type: task\",\"status\":\"tombstone\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:21:14.71625162-08:00\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:23:00.287387199-08:00\",\"deleted_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:23:00.287387199-08:00\",\"deleted_by\":\"batch delete\",\"delete_reason\":\"batch delete\",\"original_type\":\"task\"}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-43y\",\"title\":\"Implement LLM-based prompt generator for orchestrator\",\"description\":\"PromptGenerator takes a Task and project context, calls configured LLM to generate a prompt suitable for the workflow. Uses the project's agent adapter config. Generated prompt is passed as --prompt to workflow run. See docs/plans/2026-03-03-next-features-design.md §1.\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"Given a task, produces a well-formed prompt. Uses project's configured LLM. Prompt is suitable for cloche run --prompt.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T10:42:41.321151223-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-03T11:38:08.275863287-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-03T11:38:08.275863287-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\"}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-44q\",\"title\":\"LLM Client implementation\",\"description\":\"CommandLLMClient that shells out to claude -p for evolution LLM calls. See Task 17 in docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"estimated_minutes\":10,\"created_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:07:52.968002091-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:41:50.602697313-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:41:50.602697313-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"labels\":[\"evolution\"],\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-44q\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-9ud\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:09:30.164783645-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-49c\",\"title\":\"SQLite RunStore adapter\",\"description\":\"SQLite implementation of RunStore and CaptureStore. See implementation plan Task 11.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.690759403-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T12:08:18.795444043-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-20T12:08:18.795444043-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"SQLite RunStore + CaptureStore with migrations\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-49c\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-kcf\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.691929875-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-4cl\",\"title\":\"Remove Orchestrator subsystem\",\"description\":\"Delete the internal/orchestrator package and all its complexity: Orchestrator struct, HostRunner, RunWaiter, ProjectConfig, OnRunComplete callbacks, in-flight tracking, concurrency limits, task claiming, and the orchestrate RPC. Replace with the simple model: daemon runs the main workflow from host.cloche using the shared workflow engine. The main workflow manages its own looping and task selection.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-09T10:10:43.379251455-07:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-09T12:53:23.430330104-07:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-09T12:53:23.430330104-07:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-4cl\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-5dd\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-09T10:11:19.636855236-07:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-4eh\",\"title\":\"Wire cloched daemon binary\",\"description\":\"Daemon main: gRPC server, SQLite store, Unix socket listener, graceful shutdown. See implementation plan Task 15.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":0,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.852314324-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T13:22:06.36508835-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-20T13:22:06.36508835-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-4eh\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-95g\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.853504403-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"},{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-4eh\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-l1z\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.855135445-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-4ie\",\"title\":\"Daemon trigger and debounce\",\"description\":\"Evolution trigger with per-project+workflow debounce, mutex to prevent concurrent passes. Wire into trackRun() in gRPC server. See Task 18 in docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"estimated_minutes\":25,\"created_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:07:53.005657166-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-24T11:09:26.969048189-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-24T11:09:26.969048189-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"labels\":[\"evolution\"],\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-4ie\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-y5x\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:09:30.200543366-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"},{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-4ie\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-59l\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:09:30.237425411-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"},{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-4ie\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-0yn\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:09:30.272518315-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-4qd\",\"title\":\"Replace NextStep with NextSteps\",\"description\":\"- type: task\",\"status\":\"tombstone\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:21:14.712559443-08:00\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:23:00.287387199-08:00\",\"deleted_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:23:00.287387199-08:00\",\"deleted_by\":\"batch delete\",\"delete_reason\":\"batch delete\",\"original_type\":\"task\"}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-52f\",\"title\":\"Run and Capture domain types\",\"description\":\"Run, StepExecution, RunState types with lifecycle methods. See implementation plan Task 3.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.349277238-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T12:05:00.4109792-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-20T12:05:00.4109792-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Run, StepExecution types with lifecycle methods\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-52f\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-fv2\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.350429185-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-59l\",\"title\":\"Daemon capture storage\",\"description\":\"Update trackRun() to extract and store new fields from status messages. Set ProjectDir on run record. See Task 7 in docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"estimated_minutes\":15,\"created_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:07:35.32137865-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:41:50.493099344-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:41:50.493099344-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"labels\":[\"evolution\"],\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-59l\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-d3p\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:09:29.744330962-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"},{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-59l\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-myv\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:09:29.78002563-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-5bj\",\"title\":\"Update example workflows\",\"description\":\"Rename pass to success in all example workflows. Update fix step results. Update wiring accordingly. Implementation plan Task 11.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:25:12.45023414-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:54:37.915671326-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:54:37.915674693-08:00\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-5bj\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-2nb\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:25:12.452228195-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"},{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-5bj\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-88j\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:25:12.45529421-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-5dd\",\"title\":\"Unify workflow engine between cloched and cloche-agent\",\"description\":\"cloched and cloche-agent both parse and execute workflows but use completely different code paths. The host runner in the orchestrator is a bespoke reimplementation of what cloche-agent already does. Refactor so both share the same workflow parser, graph walker, and step runner — the only difference should be the environment (host vs container). This eliminates the duplicated logic that keeps breaking.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-09T10:10:31.885481297-07:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-09T12:40:35.55677421-07:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-09T12:40:35.55677421-07:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-5dd\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-r96\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-09T10:11:19.589368657-07:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-5jq\",\"title\":\"Update Run model for concurrent steps\",\"description\":\"Replace CurrentStep with ActiveSteps []string in domain.Run. Update RecordStepStart/RecordStepComplete. Fix all callers. Implementation plan Task 9.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:25:12.369774283-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:54:37.880612017-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:54:37.880615303-08:00\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-5jq\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-1r0\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:25:12.370864647-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-5yt\",\"title\":\"Update runner and status reporting\",\"description\":\"- type: task\",\"status\":\"tombstone\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:21:14.718466959-08:00\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:23:00.287387199-08:00\",\"deleted_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:23:00.287387199-08:00\",\"deleted_by\":\"batch delete\",\"delete_reason\":\"batch delete\",\"original_type\":\"task\"}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-6e9\",\"title\":\"Add cloche delete command for container removal\",\"description\":\"Add 'cloche delete \\u003ccontainer-or-run-id\\u003e' CLI command. Accepts Docker container name/ID or run ID. Calls daemon via new DeleteContainer gRPC RPC. Daemon calls docker rm and updates SQLite. Single container at a time. See docs/plans/2026-03-03-next-features-design.md §5.\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"cloche delete accepts container ID or run ID. Container is removed. SQLite record updated.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T10:41:59.761005025-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-03T12:52:21.676887164-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-03T12:52:21.676887164-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-6e9\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-toz\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T10:45:38.582029929-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-6lt\",\"title\":\"Implement merge agent (LLM-driven merge in git worktree)\",\"description\":\"Merge agent runs on the host in a git worktree. Given a branch name, it: creates a worktree, pulls latest main, merges the feature branch, resolves conflicts via LLM, runs validation if configured, merges to main on success. On success: cleans up worktree and deletes the branch. On failure: marks merge as failed, preserves branch, notifies via dashboard/indicator lights. See docs/plans/2026-03-03-next-features-design.md §1 Merge Queue.\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"Merge agent creates worktree, merges branch, resolves conflicts. Success: branch deleted, worktree cleaned. Failure: branch preserved, merge marked failed.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T11:00:40.12111266-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-03T17:08:13.380584248-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-03T17:08:13.380584248-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-6lt\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-req\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T11:01:15.431388653-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-6vs\",\"title\":\"Add container status to dashboard run detail page\",\"description\":\"Run detail page shows whether the container is still available. If so, shows a 'Delete container' button. Project overview shows count of retained containers. See docs/plans/2026-03-03-next-features-design.md §5.\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"Run detail shows container availability. Delete button works. Project cards show retained container count.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T10:42:30.941042115-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-03T12:52:21.748717246-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-03T12:52:21.748717246-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-6vs\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-toz\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T10:45:38.540717126-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-76q\",\"title\":\"Full integration test pass\",\"description\":\"Run go test and go vet to verify everything works end to end. Fix any remaining issues. Implementation plan Task 12.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:25:12.493851051-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T21:02:28.815866163-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-20T21:02:28.815868458-08:00\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-76q\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-h9t\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:25:12.495079326-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"},{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-76q\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-5bj\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:25:12.496694304-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-78b\",\"title\":\"Bug: Orchestrator ignores beads dependency graph — dispatches blocked tasks\",\"description\":\"The orchestrator's ListReady call returned tasks that have unsatisfied blocking dependencies. Tasks like cloche-07g (blocked by cloche-2cc, cloche-9ea, cloche-dzz) and cloche-208 (blocked by cloche-07g) were dispatched even though their blockers were still open.\\n\\nEither the beads tracker's ListReady implementation doesn't check the dependency graph, or the orchestrator is calling the wrong method. This caused tasks to run before their prerequisites were complete, leading to incorrect implementations and merge conflicts.\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"- ListReady only returns tasks whose blocking dependencies are all closed/completed\\n- Tasks with open blockers are never dispatched by the orchestrator\\n- Verify with a test: create task A blocking task B, confirm B is not returned by ListReady\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":0,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T13:15:00.028458264-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-06T14:49:12.854707838-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-06T14:49:12.854707838-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\"}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-7qu\",\"title\":\"Add OutputMapping and OutputPath types to domain\",\"description\":\"Add OutputMapping (EnvVar + OutputPath) and OutputPath (list of PathSegments) types to internal/domain/workflow.go. Add OutputMap field to Wire struct. Implement Evaluate([]byte) method on OutputPath that navigates JSON using field access and array indexing. Unit test path evaluation.\",\"design\":\"docs/plans/2026-03-09-wire-output-mapping-design.md\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-09T15:14:57.207446372-07:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-09T15:42:37.814276279-07:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-09T15:42:37.814276279-07:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"labels\":[\"domain\",\"dsl\"],\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-7qu\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-r3e\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-09T15:15:10.73732184-07:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-88j\",\"title\":\"Update prompt adapter to use result extraction\",\"description\":\"Inject result selection instructions into assembled prompt and use protocol.ExtractResult to parse LLM output. Remove resultOrDefault. Update tests. Implementation plan Task 5.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:24:52.067985163-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:39:43.966435416-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:39:43.966438292-08:00\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-88j\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-8ze\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:24:52.069151601-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-8bi\",\"title\":\"DSL lexer\",\"description\":\"Tokenizer for the Cloche workflow DSL. Token types, Lexer with NextToken(). See implementation plan Task 4.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.389025368-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T12:05:00.44646389-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-20T12:05:00.44646389-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Lexer with all token types, comments, arrows\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-8bi\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-fv2\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.390262837-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-8td\",\"title\":\"Add domain types for Collect\",\"description\":\"- type: task\",\"status\":\"tombstone\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:21:14.711618079-08:00\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:23:00.287387199-08:00\",\"deleted_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:23:00.287387199-08:00\",\"deleted_by\":\"batch delete\",\"delete_reason\":\"batch delete\",\"original_type\":\"task\"}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-8ze\",\"title\":\"Add result extraction protocol\",\"description\":\"Create internal/protocol/result.go with ExtractResult function that scans output for CLOCHE_RESULT marker. Last marker wins. Returns clean output with markers stripped. Implementation plan Task 3.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:24:24.152958495-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:31:16.342627663-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-20T20:31:16.342630989-08:00\"}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-8zs\",\"title\":\"Chore: initialize .cloche/version in cloche project\",\"description\":\"After cloche-9ea merges, create .cloche/version with content '1' in the cloche project repo. Commit and push so the file is tracked. The daemon will then start incrementing it on future evolution cycles.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T11:42:26.76039592-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-06T14:24:45.390243196-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-06T14:24:45.390243196-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-8zs\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-9ea\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T11:42:48.08690651-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-95g\",\"title\":\"gRPC server (daemon side)\",\"description\":\"ClocheServer implementing the gRPC service with RunStore backend. See implementation plan Task 13.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.77088948-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-20T13:05:56.205201841-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-20T13:05:56.205201841-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-95g\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-49c\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.772095809-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"},{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-95g\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-nq9\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T11:04:18.77372075-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-9ea\",\"title\":\"Project versioning: increment .cloche/version on evolution changes\",\"description\":\"After the evolution pipeline makes any change to workflow or prompt files, increment the integer in .cloche/version. File starts at 1 (created by cloche init). See docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-versioning-design.md.\",\"design\":\"docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-versioning-design.md\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"- .cloche/version is created with content '1' by cloche init\\n- config.LoadVersion(projectDir) reads and returns the version\\n- evolution/orchestrator.go increments the version when len(result.Changes) \\u003e 0\\n- Version is exposed in /api/projects/{name}/info response\\n- .cloche/version is not gitignored\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T11:25:03.406211132-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-07T18:50:08.138606886-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-07T18:50:08.138606886-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\"}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-9lt\",\"title\":\"Move project runs URL to projects/\\u003cproject\\u003e/runs\",\"description\":\"Viewing runs for a project is currently at runs?project=... but should be at projects/\\u003cproject\\u003e/runs for cleaner URL structure.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-07T19:16:54.288923031-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-09T13:27:40.485633014-07:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-09T13:27:40.485633014-07:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\"}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-9ud\",\"title\":\"Evolution Collector stage\",\"description\":\"Gather runs since last evolution, knowledge base, current prompts, current workflow. See Task 9 in docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"estimated_minutes\":20,\"created_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:07:52.658144322-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:34:26.658653494-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:34:26.658653494-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"labels\":[\"evolution\"],\"dependencies\":[{\"issue_id\":\"cloche-9ud\",\"depends_on_id\":\"cloche-sdc\",\"type\":\"blocks\",\"created_at\":\"2026-02-24T10:09:29.815486827-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\"}]}","numLines":50,"startLine":1,"totalLines":134}}}
